{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Falloff"], "type": "title", "extent": [98, 110], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [110, 163], "text": ["Adds smooth distance attributes to geometry."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [163, 496], "text": ["Falloff generates attributes for the distance between points and the input group\nof points on the input surface geometry, similar to the falloff visualizer of\n", {"text": ["Soft Transform"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/softxform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/softxform"}, ". Distance can be measured with a variety of\nmetrics to produce different results, and a falloff can be applied to smooth the\nattribute."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [531, 579], "text": ["Subset of points to measure distance from."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "group"}, "extent": [508, 515], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [606, 654], "text": ["The format for the ", {"text": ["Distance Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [668, 836], "text": ["Distance is output between 0 and ", {"text": ["Radius"], "type": "ui"}, ", with points outside the\n        ", {"text": ["Radius"], "type": "ui"}, " having the same value as a point on the boundary of the\n        radius."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance"], "extent": [654, 668], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [861, 1013], "text": ["Distance is output between 0 and 1, with points outside the ", {"text": [" Radius"], "type": "ui"}, "\n        having the same value as a point on the boundary of the radius."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Normalized Distance"], "extent": [836, 861], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1037, 1158], "text": ["Distance is measured over the entire model. This cannot be reversed\n        since there is no maximum distance."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Unbounded Distance"], "extent": [1013, 1037], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Type"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "outputtype"}, "extent": [579, 585], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1196, 1258], "text": ["Method for measuring which points are within the radius."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1277, 1369], "text": ["The shortest distance to a point in the group following a path along\n        edges."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Edge Distance"], "extent": [1258, 1277], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1381, 1440], "text": ["The 3D distance to the closest point in the group."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Radius"], "extent": [1369, 1381], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1462, 1621], "text": ["The shortest distance to a point in the group following a path along\n        the surface of the input geometry, both along edges and across polygons."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Surface Distance"], "extent": [1440, 1462], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance Metric"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "distmetric"}, "extent": [1158, 1175], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1666, 1710], "text": ["Maximum distance to search for points."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/radius", "id": "rad"}, "extent": [1621, 1629], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1737, 1802], "text": ["Apply the ramp from right to left instead of left to right."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Reverse"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "reverse"}, "extent": [1710, 1719], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1837, 1993], "text": ["A selection of useful ramp presets which change the ", {"text": ["Ramp"], "type": "ui"}, " value. When\n    changes are made to a preset, the changes are saved in the Custom preset."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Ramp Presets"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "ramppreset"}, "extent": [1802, 1816], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2014, 2188], "text": ["The ramp used to smooth the ", {"text": ["Distance Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, ". The left side of the\n    ramp is applied to points closer to the source group, unless ", {"text": ["Reverse"], "type": "ui"}, " is\n    toggled on."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Ramp"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "ramp"}, "extent": [1993, 1999], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2213, 2315], "text": ["The method used to combine new values with preexisting values of the\n    ", {"text": ["Distance Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2328, 2383], "text": ["The maximum of the new and old values is kept."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Maximum"], "extent": [2315, 2328], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2396, 2451], "text": ["The minimum of the new and old values is kept."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Minimum"], "extent": [2383, 2396], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2461, 2658], "text": ["The new values are kept within the ", {"text": ["Radius"], "type": "ui"}, " and the old values are\n        kept outside the ", {"text": ["Radius"], "type": "ui"}, ". Note that this can cause very sharp changes\n        in the ", {"text": ["Distance Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["None"], "extent": [2451, 2461], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2673, 2718], "text": ["All preexisting values are ignored."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Overwrite"], "extent": [2658, 2673], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Mix Method"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "mix"}, "extent": [2188, 2200], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2757, 3118], "text": ["If given, a point attribute with the specified name will be created,\n    indicating the distance from the input group at each point. If ", {"text": ["Output\n    Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is ", {"text": ["Normalized Distance"], "type": "ui"}, " the value will be between 0 and 1, with\n    lower values being farther from the input group. Otherwise the value will be\n    the measured distance from the input group."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "distattr"}, "extent": [2718, 2738], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3161, 3302], "text": ["If given, a point attribute with the specified name will be created,\n    indicating the closest point in the input group at each point."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Lead Point Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "leadptattr"}, "extent": [3118, 3140], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3341, 3481], "text": ["If given, a point group with the specified name will be created, indicating\n    which points are within ", {"text": ["Radius"], "type": "ui"}, " of the input group."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Affected Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "falloffgroup"}, "extent": [3302, 3318], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3488, 3722], "text": ["When using the edge or surface ", {"text": ["Distance Metric"], "type": "ui"}, " with the unbounded raw\n    distance ", {"text": ["Output Type"], "type": "ui"}, ", points that are disconnected from geometry\n    containing the source group will have a ", {"text": ["Distance Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, " value of ", {"text": ["-1"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [3481, 3488], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [496, 508], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3731, 3755], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/softxform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/softxform"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3755, 3777], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/softpeak", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/softpeak"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3777, 3795], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/edit", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/edit"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [3722, 3731], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Adds smooth distance attributes to geometry."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "smooth, tech", "since": "17.0", "namespace": null, "internal": "falloff", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/falloff"}, "title": ["Falloff"]}